A message set with "fail()" can leak into following "it()" if an async method is mistakenly called by user (e.g., if one is not aware some 3rd party callback is async).
Happens with "fail()" messages only, not with "expect()" messages.
https://plnkr.co/edit/qfZCXMBM8IiA2AsvQwGu
The spec is also included below.
